    • Method Detail

      • analyzeMemberRedundancy

        public static RefSetMemberRedundancyAnalyzer.ReferencedComponentIdSet analyzeMemberRedundancy(@Nonnull
                                                                                              SnomedRegularRefSet refSet,
                                                                                              @Nullable
                                                                                              org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor,
                                                                                              java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String> componentIds)
        Returns with a a set of redundant and non-redundant member IDs based on the specified SNOMED CT reference set and the terminology independent component identifier.

        Note: this method does nothing but returns with the specified componentIds wrapped to a RefSetMemberRedundancyAnalyzer.ReferencedComponentIdSet instance since redundancy based on the referenced components is not available for SNOMED CT simple map type and SNOMED CT complex map type reference sets. This method throws IllegalStateException if the specified SNOMED CT reference set is a query type reference set.
        Parameters:
        refSet - the reference where the member redundancy analysis should be performed.
        monitor - the progress monitor for the process. Can be null. If null a new NullProgressMonitor will be instantiated.
        componentIds - the terminology independent component identifiers.
        Returns:
        the RefSetMemberRedundancyAnalyzer.ReferencedComponentIdSet wrapping the redundant and non-redundant reference set member IDs.
